#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
final_pipeline.py — Token-Level PDF Reconstruction Pipeline
=============================================================

Architecture (NO table detection):
  1. CLASSIFY pages as NATIVE_TEXT or IMAGE_ONLY.
  2. NATIVE pages → copy directly from original PDF.
  3. SCANNED pages → extract tokens → render at original positions → PDF.
  4. MERGE all pages into final output PDF.
  5. NUMERIC COLUMN analysis for QA (no structure creation).
  6. LOG + QA HTML output.

Key principles:
  • Every token rendered at its exact original position.
  • No grid/border/table detection. No region classification.
  • Numeric tokens preserve x-position and digit order.
  • RTL for Arabic text, LTR for numbers.
  • Scanned and native pages behave identically.

Usage:
    python final_pipeline.py
    python final_pipeline.py --input "el-bankalahly .pdf" --output final_output.pdf
"""

